bug.short_desc: [TracWiki] multiple lines support in list items

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 221338 TracWiki Rendering from the examples. Created with http://trac.edgewall.org/demo-1.0/
The Trac parser do not support list items over multiple lines. (as mentioned in Bug 389812)
See user manual of Trac WikiFormatting for lists: http://trac.edgewall.org/demo-1.0/wiki/WikiFormatting#Lists
Examples (see also screenshot for the Trac rendering):
== testListMultipleLines ==
* an item with 2 lines * other second line * ok? And a new paragraph
== testListMultipleLinesWithoutSpacePrefix ==
- an item create paragraph - try this again - it is working - ok?
== testListMultipleLinesBigSpacePrefix ==
1. item1 more lines 1. item2
== testListMultipleLinesQuote ==
1. item1 wrong: create a quote 1. item2
Closed as part of backlog clean-up. Please re-open if you'd like to see this revisited, perhaps with a contribution.

As discussed on the mailing list [1], I reopen this bug.
Please review the Gerrit Change [2].
[1] http://dev.eclipse.org/mhonarc/lists/mylyn-docs-dev/msg00180.html [2] https://git.eclipse.org/r/7865
